author: app.com
title: Football roundup: Freehold & Monmouth edge the competition
text:
MORE A non-divisional clash between Freehold Boro and Wall Township fell in favor of the Colonials by a score of 14-7.
The Colonials (4-2) held a 14-0 advantage over the Crimson Knights (1-5) at the half, and Freehold’s senior quarterback Jake Curry had a hand in both scoring strikes.
Curry’s day opened with a 40-yard touchdown toss to freshman wide out Matt Krauss, before scampering into the end zone from 23 yards out.
The Freehold defense put forth a stout effort and was led by senior Mendelle Tims and junior Markee Gill, who each recorded an interception.
Freehold will host Toms River East in another non-divisional matchup in Week 7 with a 1 p.m. tilt on Oct. 24, while Wall will look to rebound on Oct. 23 when it welcomes Class B North foe Neptune to town on Oct. 23.
Monmouth 14, JFK Iselin 9: After trailing 3-0 at the half, Malik Wiggins returned the opening kick of the third quarter 70 yards to spark the Monmouth offense, as the Falcons punched the ball into the end zone three plays later on an eight-yard touchdown carry by Ely Velez.
Casey Pachuki helped extend the lead to 14-3 in fourth quarter with a 17-yard scoring carry.
The Monmouth defense stood strong throughout this non-conference matchup, holding its opponent to less than 100 yards of total offense, an effort fronted by senior Ciaran Hoffman, who recorded four tackles for a loss.
